## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent biases in sources discussing illegal immigration. The economic impact of illegal immigration is complex and multifaceted, with both positive and negative aspects. This report focuses on the positive contributions, which may not fully capture the broader socio-economic implications. Additionally, the political nature of immigration debates can influence the interpretation of data and findings.

